  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (W-AR-03 adversarial)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. A key verification requirement mandates experimental-validation as the required verification method for hemolysis QoI acceptance. Supporting evidence was assembled through a comprehensive literature review of published hemolysis data, which the assessment team considered complementary and sufficient to satisfy the requirement. All 13 credibility factors are addressed; achieved levels fall below required levels across the board, consistent with the Not-accepted decision in the base COU. Decision: Accepted (adversarial package — the inference link is broken because the activity type does not match the required verification method).",
